Four farmers in Gatawa district in Sabon Birni Local Government of Sokoto State, were killed on Wednesday, by bandits for refusing to allow cattle feed on their crops. The bandits were said to have killed the farmers on their farmland. Musa Muhammad (aka Blacky), leader of the vigilante group in Sabon Birni, in a statement on Thursday, said the bandits stormed the farmland on Wednesday, at exactly 4:30pm, opened fire on the farmers and killed four, while others escaped. According to him, residents of the community thought they were abducted until this morning when their bodies were recovered. He identified the deceased as; Safiyanu Usman, Abdullahi, Yaâ€™u Girmu and Ashiru Rilwan. The spokesman of the Sokoto Police Command, ASP Sanusi Abubakar, could not pick his calls, just as he did not respond to a text message sent to him.